;Web literacy should be as foundational to education as reading, writing, and math – and it should be taught everywhere learning happens.
Ri Ajk'amaya'l choltz'ib'anem k'o chi yalan rejqalem pa tijonïk achi'el ri sik'inem, ri tz'ib'anïk chuqa' ri ajilanem – chuqa' k'o chi nik'ut xab'akuchi' nik'ulwachitäj ri k'utunïk.


;Learning Web literacy is like any other essential skill: we learn best by doing. And in the digital world, learning happens not just with teachers in the classroom, but everywhere there’s an Internet connection. We need all kinds of educators to have the knowledge and resources to teach Web literacy the way kids learn it best. And we need to make sure every student grows up not just on the Web, but fluent in the way it works.
Ri retamaxik Ajk'amaya'l choltz'ibanem achi'el xab'achike k'atzinel etamab'äl: ütz niqetamaj toq niqasamajij. Pa ri kemtz'ib' ruwach'ulew, man netamäx ta xa xe kik'in ri tijonela' pa tijonijay ruma chi xab'akuchi' k'o okem pa K'amaya'l. K'atzinel chi qe chi jalajöj kiwa ri tijonela' richin niqetamaj chuqa' nik'oje' tob'äl richin niqak'üt ri Ajk'amaya'l choltz'ib'anem achi'el jeb'ël niketamaj ri ak'wala'. Chuqa' k'o chi niqajikib'a' chi ri tijoxela' man kek'ïy xa xe pa Ajk'amaya'l, xa chuqa' jeb'ël tusamajij rub'eyal nisamäj.


